OL,3,CPregnant women in ICU face 12-times
OL,4,Chigher rate of stillbirth
OL,6,FAlmost one in 500, some 1,449 women,
OL,7,Fwere admitted to intensive care, which
OL,8,Fresearchers found increased their risk
OL,9,Fof having a stillbirth, along with a
OL,10,F40-times higher risk of death than
OL,11,Fthose not admitted.
OL,13,FThe most common reason for admission
OL,14,Fto ICU was postpartum haemorrhage,
OL,15,Fheavier bleeding than normal after
OL,16,Fbirth, while the most frequent cause
OL,17,Fof death was cardiovascular disease.
